    dcterms:description "The project aims to develop an open-access digital gazetteer for place names in Hebrew script, creating a comprehensive and interoperable database of historical toponyms. By providing a stable digital reference accessible via its website and API, Kima facilitates scholarly research and integration with tools like the Pelagios annotation and mapping environment Recogito."@en ;
