    dcterms:description "The Mamluk Bibliography Online is a digital humanities resource offering a comprehensive, searchable database of bibliographic records on Mamluk studies. Divided into primary and secondary resources, it allows users to search by authors or subjects, streamlining access to scholarly materials for research on Mamluk history and culture."@en ;
