    dcterms:created "2024-11-28"^^xsd:date ;
    dcterms:description "The project focuses on the Islamic culture of the Horn of Africa, exploring the region's rich but under-researched literary heritage. It applies digital humanities approaches to catalog, digitize, and analyze manuscripts written in Arabic and local languages using Arabic script. The project has created a comprehensive database that documents over 4,000 texts, shedding light on the region's Islamic traditions and intellectual history while enhancing the preservation of its written heritage​."@en ;
