    dcterms:created "2022-09-05"^^xsd:date ;
    dcterms:description "This digital collection provides access to one of the earliest written sub-Saharan languages in manuscript form - Old Kanembu written in Arabic script was a language of Qur’anic interpretation in the ancient Borno Sultanate. The digitalized corpus contains more than 5000 folios of Old Kanembu Islamic manuscripts from Nigeria, Niger and Republic of Chad and is an outcome of three research projects conducted in SOAS University of London and University Hamburg."@en ;
