    dcterms:description "PALEOCORAN examines Qur’anic manuscripts that once belonged to the ‘Amr ibn al-‘Āṣ Mosque in al-Fusṭāṭ (Old Cairo) – one of the most significant Qur’anic Libraries – and are now scattered across the globe. The main objective of the project is to reconstruct the library and to make the manuscripts available digitally."@en ;
