    dcterms:created "2022-11-04"^^xsd:date ;
    dcterms:description "This project is a collaboration between Cuneiform Digital Library Initiative (CDLI) and a German researcher Klaudia Englund and is dedicated to the digital preservation of the heritage of the Nimrud palace, which suffered severe damage at the hands of ISIS. The main goal of the project lies in preparing for display the image and text files that the researcher gathered in the course of her work on the Northwest Palace and the over 600 relief slabs mounted along the walls of the building’s main rooms."@en ;
    dcterms:hasPart <https://closingthegap.org/id/project/b8097890-6eeb-43ba-890d-28e1490fde08> ;
